<br>
Is there any way I can pull them where only 1 or 2 mobs will aggro?  I was thinking of standing as far back as I could next to the water and casting Malisement or a low level nuke and then sending my pet in as soon as the mobs started to head towards me.<br>
<br>
Thanks  <p>Kebkin <!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=551328" target="top">My gear</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stren>Stren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 93<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 9:22:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=336.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about soloing the entrance to The Hole</span><hr size=1> I never did the Hole, but there's a lot of threads about it if you go back a few pages.<br>
<br>
If memory serves, you have the right idea of pulling with Malisment and running back to your pet, but my memory plays tricks on me.<br>
<br>
Use Search.  It's your friend.<br>
<br>
I'm a firm believer that Neriak exp is the best at these levels. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=coddington>Coddington</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#333333>(2/14/03 1:06:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=336.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Question about soloing the entrance to The Hole</span><hr size=1> Here, let me try:<br>
<br>
After you zone and summon your pet, walk to where you can first see the first mob on the far right wall (they're paired up against the long walls until the downward slope) and cast somthing at the mob (1st level Flame spell is my favorite).  He'll follow you and sick your pet on him.  Once he's dead, walk further into corridor and aggro the next Elemental.  No need to cast if you've got KoS, just let him aggro you.  Once he's dead, stand in his spawn spot and cast on the mob opposite him further down the hall.  Continue this until you've got all the mobs.  You may get aggro from the first two because you're so close and make sure the mob dies before he aggroes the other mobs further down the hall.<br>
<br>
There is better decriptions (with pictures!) on this list, but hopefully this'll do.  Good luck!<br>
<br>
Coddington<br>
lvl 54 Mage<br>
Terris-Thule<br>
